programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Sofia Central Prison, Sofia, Bulgaria
programme.desc: With a crumbling foundation fit for demolition, Sofia Central prison is inhospitable for anyone, including criminals. With multiple prisoner cells, bunks stacked 3 high and horrid isolation cells, prisoners live idly behind bars for 23 hours a day.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Miami, Dade County Jail Boot Camp, Miami, Florida, USA
programme.desc: The toughest divisions of the Miami Dade: Boot Camp gives minor offenders a chance to escape the prison through unforgiving drills and rules. To many it is a better alternative to The M-D County Jail where murderers and rapists have their own rules.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: On the coast of Queensland, Australia, rumors of something unique have haunted locals for centuries. Aboriginal cave paintings depict a large and furry bipedal monster. European colonists reported a similar creature stalking the woods. What is Yowie?

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The beauty of Australia’s Byron Bay attracts over one million visitors per year. However, they probably don’t suspect the presence of a mysterious creature known locally as the Devil Dog. It could be an animal long thought extinct, the Tasmanian tiger.

programme.title: Caught on Camera
programme.desc: Host Nick Wallis reveals some of the street crime captured by London's 100,000 CCTV cameras: Fights, robberies, drug crimes and a massive gun rampage.

programme.title: Countdown to Catastrophe: Volcanoes
programme.desc: Mount Nyiragongo stands an altitude of 3500 meters with lava that boils at 1000.

programme.title: Countdown to Catastrophe: Earthquakes
programme.desc: In many countries of the world people are so used to earthquakes that a little jolt of the ground barely raises an eyebrow. But since the Fukushima nuclear reactor disaster the issue of seismic security has taken on new urgency.

programme.title: Countdown to Catastrophe: Storms
programme.desc: What impact do hurricanes make on the global climate? Geophysicist Shimon Wdowinski from the University of Miami has discovered a truly astonishing connection: major storms can trigger massive earthquakes.

programme.title: Death on the Matterhorn
programme.desc: Seven men stand on the summit of the Matterhorn, the last Alpine peak to be conquered. Their place in history is assured. Then, disaster strikes: a rope snaps. Four men die. But did the rope really just snap...or was it cut?

programme.title: Mont Saint-Michel: Resistance Through the Ages
programme.desc: Mont Saint-Michel has stood in the middle of a vast bay off the French coast of Normandy for centuries. It has become a symbol of resistance to the test of time. This film offers a journey through the history and mysteries of this indomitable fortress.

programme.title: Human Prey: Deadly Waters
programme.desc: While on the job at an Florida golf club, an experienced golf ball diver is attacked by a territorial, 400-pound alligator. Jeff Tanswell's snorkeling trip turns into a bloody battle for his life when he is dragged under by an 12-foot saltwater crocodile.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killer Canines and Felines
programme.desc: On a camping trip in the Canadian wilderness, a family is unwittingly stalked by a hungry and opportunistic wolf. A mountain bike excursion in California becomes a life-and-death struggle when a cyclist is pounced and attacked upon by a 110 pound cougar.

programme.title: Stir Of Echoes
programme.desc: After being hypnotized by his sister-in-law, a man begins seeing haunting visions of a girl's ghost and a mystery begins to unfold around him. Starring: Kevin Bacon, Zachary David Cope, Kathryn Erbe, Illeana Douglas, Kevin Dunn.

programme.title: The Ninth Gate
programme.desc: A rare book dealer, while seeking out the last two copies of a demon text, gets drawn into a conspiracy with supernatural overtones. Starring: Johnny Depp, Frank Langella, Lena Olin.

programme.title: The Little Ghost
programme.desc: The Little Ghost lives in the castle over looking a small town and awakens for precisely one hour after the clock strikes midnight. Follow him on this adventure to see his first sunrise ever!

programme.title: The Christmas Consultant
programme.desc: This Lifetime Original Movie stars David Hasselhoff as a sought after consultant hired by a workaholic mother (Caroline Rhea) in an effort to get her and her family through the holidays.

programme.title: Heaven Sent
programme.desc: Maire prays that her husband find the strength to let go of their 9 year marriage. Billy is asking that his wife receive the strength and wisdom to hold on. A 8-year-old runaway from heaven takes it upon herself to rekindle the romance that slipped away.

programme.title: Wishin' and Hopin'
programme.desc: Based on the New York Times best-selling Christmas novel by Wally Lamb comes the new Christmas classic, starring Molly Ringwald and featuring Chevy Chase as the narrator.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Manhunt In Space
programme.desc: Manhunt In Space: An early episode of the soap opera behemoth General Hospital plus a movie made of several TV episodes about space pirates.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Danger Death Ray
programme.desc: Danger Death Ray: A slick secret agent investigates an evil organization that stole a top secret death ray.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Samson vs. The Vampire Women
programme.desc: While Mike and the Bots wrestle with Samson vs. the Vampire Women, TV's Frank is assumed into Second Banana Heaven.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Violent Years
programme.desc: Jam Handy shows the world the glory of sexism with electric kitchen appliances and Ed Wood analyzes the world of criminals spoiled by their parents.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Incredibly Strange Creatures Who Stopped Living and Became Mixed-Up Zombies
programme.desc: A couple of slackers stumble across a cult of monsters at a carnival.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Gorgo
programme.desc: Greedy sailors capture a giant lizard off the coast of Ireland and sell it to a London circus. Then its mother shows up.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Devil Fish
programme.desc: When Dr. Stella Dickens concludes the recent string of grisly deaths and demolished boats can’t be the result of any known marine creature, she sets out to capture the beast, a genetically created bioweapon that must be kept secret . . . at any cost.

programme.title: Fun in Balloon Land
programme.desc: We would say that Fun In Balloonland is our favourite RiffTrax movie, but there's just one problem: it's hard to really describe it as a movie. It is an event. To attempt to describe its plot to you, would be like attempting to divide by zero.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Planet of Dinosaurs
programme.desc: Planet of Dinosaurs: When a spaceship full of hairy people crashes on an unknown planet, they must forge off on a non-stop mission of wandering around doing nothing in particular.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Bloody Pit of Horror
programme.desc: Filmed in PSYCHOVISION, (which we hear Fellini used to shoot in), Bloody Pit of Horror is must see Italian horror at its cheesiest. Mike, Kevin and Bill brave the spider piñata and give it their bloody best.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Brainiac: Brainiac
programme.desc: Back in 1661, a Spanish baron in the middle of burning at the stake escaped by hitching a ride on a passing comet. And now he returns, 300 years later, a shapeshifting monstrosity bent on killing the descendants of those who wronged him as The Brainiac.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Alien Outlaw
programme.desc: Predator costumes, Lash LaRue AND his fat hillbilly sidekick buddy from The Dark Power, an alien killed with a fishing hook, what more could anyone ask for. It's time for befuddlement and laughter, join Mike, Kevin and Bill for Alien Outlaw!

programme.title: RiffTrax: The Revenge of Dr X: The Revenge of Dr X
programme.desc: It's a cautionary tale about the limits of science, the corrupting forces of power and of course, mainly about getting Ed Wood involved in your movie. Mike, Kevin and Bill team up to riff the botanical masterwork, The Revenge of Doctor X.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Buffalo Rider: Buffalo Rider
programme.desc: Buffalo Rider: When you really stop and think about it, there are two kinds of movies: movies where rugged men punch mountain lions, and movies where this sadly does not happen.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy Is Getting Married
programme.desc: Oggy is in Venice with Olivia, the perfect setting for a marriage proposal. Jack is there too... and the roaches, of course.

programme.title: Sandra the Fairytale Detective: Pesky Rodents / Assaf the Magician
programme.desc: Sandra and Fo go into the tale of the 'Pied Piper of Hamelin'. There, they discover that something very strange has happened in the story. / On this occasion, Sandra and Fo travel into the tale of 'Aladdin and the Magic Lamp'.

programme.title: Sandra the Fairytale Detective: Royal Egg / Frogs
programme.desc: Everybody knows the story of the 'Ugly Duckling' but nobody knows how the swan’s egg ended up in a duck’s nest. Sandra and Fo have to resolve this mystery. / Sandra and Fo travel into the story of the 'Frog Prince' to look for an antidote.

programme.title: Sandra the Fairytale Detective: Toy Room / A Question of Smell
programme.desc: Sandra and Fo travel into the story of the 'Steadfast Tin Soldier' where they hope to prevent the Soldier and the Ballerina from being thrown into the fire. / In 'Jack and the Beanstalk' Sandra and Fo climb up into the strange world of the giants ...

programme.title: Sandra the Fairytale Detective: The 22:30 Express / King of Mortadella
programme.desc: Sandra and Fo travel into the story of 'Red Riding Hood' only to discover that the Little Red Riding Hood and her grandmother are blamed for a series of mysterious crimes ... / Sandra and Fo visit 'Pinocchio' who has inexplicably grown donkey's ears.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Unhappy Birthday / Lola Fashion
programme.desc: Lola discovers, much to her surprise, that Virginia’s birthday is on the same day as hers. / Virginia is wearing a new dress by the most prestigious fashion designer at the moment. But Lola gets all the attention with her new self-made t-shirt ...

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Magic Garden / The Secret Club
programme.desc: Lola, Poppy, and Haide are hard at work preparing a dance routine for the end-of-term show at school. / Lola, Poppy and Haide form the ‘Secrets Club’. Virginia, jealous of their friendship, manages to read the contents of their tin full of secrets.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: A Moped for Two / Perfect Friendship
programme.desc: Lola enters the Rice Speedies cereal contest. She needs to collect the most cards possible to win the moped of her dreams. / One day, Lola discovers that Oswaldo Porri, Virginia’s personal therapist, is about to allow her to return to her old school.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Headline News / Pair of Aces
programme.desc: Lola and her editorial team of the school newspaper still haven’t decided what should go on the front page. / Lola is green with envy: The school’s male and female representatives Poppy and Charly are about to spend a whole week together in Barcelona ...

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: A Shoulder to Cry on / Kinky Kindred
programme.desc: Lola falls in love with David, a boy who comes to her school on a music scholarship. But David fell head over heels in love with Virginia. / In class, during an ancestry lesson, Lola mocks Virginia, reminding her that she is related to the monkey.

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Afraid of What? / Oh No, Not Her!
programme.desc: Before watching a horror film, Lola and Virginia set a challenge to find out who is the bravest. / Lola introduces her exchange mate Chichita Gonzales to all her friends. Virginia is envious ...

programme.title: Lola & Virginia: Hugo in Love / Fan Club
programme.desc: Virginia flatters Hugo, the roughest student in the school, and he falls head over heels in love with her. / Lola is the President of the San Lorenzo branch of the Fan Club of Marco Amore, a singer who is a big favourite among teenage girls.

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: We've Got Spirit / Cedar Hills' Most Wanted
programme.desc: Trying to avoid a lice check results in Chuck accidentally causing his school to become haunted. / Jealous of Misha’s popularity, Chuck chooses to be wanted – and ends up being the most wanted person on Earth!

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: The Dark Dingo and Possum Pete / Flush Hour Two
programme.desc: When someone keeps bedazzling his locker, Chuck chooses to get help from his comic book hero: the Dark Dingo. / When U.D. accidentally flushes Misha's pet goldfish down the toilet, the gang goes into the sewer after her.

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: Bawk to the Future / Hairy Christmas
programme.desc: Desperate to get his hands on some tasty chicken, Chuck travels to the future where chickens have evolved and run society! / When a choice goes awry it's up to Chuck to save Christmas.

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: In Space, Norman Can Hear You Scream / Area Fifty-Tree
programme.desc: A choice sends Chuck and his friends to a distant planet, where Norm assumes the role of Intergalactic Champion. / Chuck and his friends come across the mysterious agents of Area Fifty Tree.

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: Joey in da House! / Art Attack
programme.desc: When Joey and Alfie have a fight, Chuck tries to get them back together or risk living with Joey forever. / Chuck makes a choice that results in his artwork coming to life before the evil art curator Constance Bagelschmidt steals it.

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: The Good, the Bad and the UD – Part 1 / The Good, the Bad and the UD – Part 2
programme.desc: Chuck and his friends visit U.D.'s home planet where Chuck must prove he has what it takes to continue being the Decider. / Chuck must save the people of G’Nooki from an invasion of Snake People and the evil Borkle.

programme.title: Chuck's Choice: Cool Hand Norm / Sunny Daze
programme.desc: Norm turns into a ruthless Ice King with an army of polar bears!! / Chuck plays the greatest baseball team in the universe, robots from outer space!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Blasts From The Past
Supa Strikas: Between Friends
programme.desc: Supa Strikas travel to Mexico to confront the biggest goalkeeper in the Super League. Shakes uncovers De Los Santos’ past, and makes an amazing discovery in the big man’s hometown: mysterious Aztec ruins ... and the origins of the game itself!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Instinct Extinct
programme.desc: Supa Strikas face Twisting Tiger’s old team, FC Nakama, but Nakama boss Ura Giri releases a DVD of all Tiger’s secret moves to punish him for leaving the team. Now the famous midfielder needs to find new moves ... and fast!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Big Bo Lockdown
programme.desc: Pressure is on as Supa Strikas arrive in Spain to play Barka FC and star striker, Riano. But Shakes gets some training from Riano’s old Coach, Golare, which turns out to be less than helpful!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The End Of Dreams
programme.desc: Big Bo helps local prison inmates by training their soccer team. But Knuckles, a nasty convict, looks just like the great goalkeeper and switches places with Big Bo! How will he escape in time for Supa Strikas’ epic game against the mighty FC Colossus?

programme.title: Supa Strikas: No 'El' in Team
programme.desc: After a mishap with the bumbling Professor, his coffee, and the state-of-the-art Match Measure Machine, things go horribly wrong with Shakes’ exercise plan!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Wolf In Coach's Clothing
programme.desc: El Matador’s selfish play causes headaches for Strikas. Coach sends him to Solinesia to learn the ancient football game that is all about teamwork. But hopes are dashed when he is banished from the country!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Teen Rebels
programme.desc: Zig finds an old skateboard in a crate. It awakens memories, taking him back to when he, Bernie, Sharko and Marina were teenagers, and all they only cared about were stunts on wheels….

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Mummy
programme.desc: A pyramid is discovered on the beach! Marina races inside. Zig and Sharko follow. Marina finds a chamber with a very friendly mummy, while Zig and Sharko get hammered by endless booby traps ...
